<body>

  <h1>üè° Buyer Journey Flow ‚Äì NoBroker</h1>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>1. CX Comes to NoBroker</h2>
    <p>Customer subscribes to the <strong>Buyer Plan</strong>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>2. An RM is Assigned</h2>
    <p>Done via automated system or assigned via a dummy RM later reassigned by TL.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>3. CX Fills Requirements in NB App</h2>
    <p>If not filled, RM collects during the OB (Onboarding) call.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>4. OB Call</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>RM builds rapport with CX</li>
      <li>Notes all requirements (budget, BHK, etc.)</li>
      <li>Explains the call patch process</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>5. Finding a Lead</h2>
    <p>Leads are sourced through:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>RM DB (active and matching leads)</li>
      <li>Google search + manual input</li>
      <li>Internal dashboard's Leads tab</li>
      <li>Similar tenant-based references</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>6. ROC (Requirement Owner Confirmation)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Availability of property</li>
      <li>Income compatibility, water, BHK, metro proximity</li>
      <li>Khata, DDA approval, builder, amenities</li>
    </ul>
    <p>ROC is completed before sharing with the buyer.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>7. Property Suggestions</h2>
    <p>Properties are shortlisted based on location and fit, then shared with CX.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>8. Lead Discussion</h2>
    <p>RM discusses all key property highlights with the CX.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>9. CX Shortlists Property</h2>
    <p>Buyer either chooses from suggestions or self-shortlists.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>10. RM Helps Schedule a Visit</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Confirms date/time with seller</li>
      <li>Shares who will show the property</li>
      <li>Details conveyed to CX</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>11. Visit Stage</h2>
    <div class="highlight">
      <strong>Scenario A - Visited:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Feedback call taken</li>
        <li>If CX likes property: RM negotiates, finalises, pitches VAS, and closes deal</li>
        <li>If not liked: RM reschedules or suggests new leads</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="highlight">
      <strong>Scenario B - Not Visited:</strong>
      <p>RM attempts to reschedule visit</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>12. BMTE (Buyer Makes The Effort)</h2>
    <p>Customer independently contacts seller and finalises deal without RM‚Äôs help.</p>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
